From 7ac29fe4fef3cc01b71bc488fe1925afa742f3b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jani Nikula <jani.nikula@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jan 2020 16:00:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4011/4530] drm/i915/pm: use intel de functions for forcewake
 register access
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Move away from I915_READ_FW() and I915_WRITE_FW() in display code, and
switch to using intel_de_read_fw() and intel_de_write_fw(),
respectively.

No functional changes.

Reviewed-by: Ville Syrjälä <ville.syrjala@linux.intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Chris Wilson <chris@chris-wilson.co.uk>
Signed-off-by: Jani Nikula <jani.nikula@intel.com>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20200123140004.14136-6-jani.nikula@intel.com
---
